<HEADLINE> Rain Returns to Interrupt Women's Play </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Rain came back to interrupt the 926,250
U.S. dollars Italian Open women's tennis tournament on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The first round matches scheduled on Monday had been delayed
for heavy rain and were put back to Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 24 matches were expected to play but only 11
contests completed, with others looking in danger to be finished
as the rain dropped in mid-afternoon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
