<HEADLINE> China to Celebrate Anniversary of Historic Party Meeting (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 5 (Xinhua) -- China will celebrate the 20th
anniversary of the Third Plenary Session of the 11th Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) on December 18
this year.
</P>
<P>
The plenary session was of vital importance in the history of
both the Party and the state, as it has reestablished the
ideological line of emancipating the mind and seeking truth from
facts, according to a circular of the CPC Central Committee which
was made public today.
</P>
<P>
The session sparked an historic change in the emphasis of
the Party's work and opened a new period for China's reforms,
opening to the outside world and concentrating on the socialist
modernization drive, according to the circular.
</P>
<P>
The past two decades have witnessed monumental achievements in
China's socialist reform, opening-up and modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
The main theme of celebrations will center on reviewing the
great achievements and experience of China's reform, opening-up
and modernization drive since the Third Plenum of the 11th CPC
Central Committee in order to enable the whole party and all
Chinese people gain a deeper understanding of Deng Xiaoping Theory
and the Party line. The event will enable people to think and act
in accordance with the guidelines of the 15th National Congress of
the CPC, rally around the Party Central Committee with Jiang Zemin
at the core, and promote the great cause of socialism with Chinese
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
The event will publicize the great significance of
reestablishing the ideological line of emancipating the mind and
seeking truth from facts; the great achievements in the economic,
political, scientific and technological, educational, cultural,
military and diplomatic fields over the past two decades under the
guidance of Deng Xiaoping Theory and the Party's basic line; the
status and guiding significance of Deng Xiaoping Theory and the
contributions the 15th Party congress made to implementing and
developing the line, policies and principles of the Third Plenum
of the 11th CPC Central Committee.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980506.0008 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Celebrate Anniversary of Historic Party Meeting (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The highlight of celebrations will be a grand ceremony in the
Great Hall of the People. CPC Central Committee General Secretary
Jiang Zemin will present the keynote speech at the ceremony which
will be sponsored by the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Other activities will include a theoretical workshop to mark
the 20th anniversary of the historic meeting. The event, scheduled
for the middle of May, will be sponsored by the Publicity
Department of the CPC Central Committee and the Central Party
School.
</P>
<P>
A seminar to mark the 20th anniversary of the discussions on
the argument that practice is the sole criterion for verifying
truth will also be held in May.
</P>
<P>
A large number of high quality literary works, films, TV
programs and performances will be released during the year. Major
Beijing-based newspapers will publish key articles and stories,
and the General Post Office will issue a set of commemorative
stamps to mark the occasion.
</P>
<P>
Celebrations will also be held by various provinces and
departments under the unified plan of the CPC central
committee. 
</P>
