<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Undertakes Study on Hydro-electric Power </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Water Resources
of Ethiopia and two Norwegian companies signed an agreement here
Monday to undertake feasibility study on Ethiopia's four rivers
with potential for hydro-electric power generation.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the study to be carried on four
rivers including Genale, Baro and Gebba will be undertaken within
five to six months.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the ministry has undertaken similar studies on the
rivers of Tekeze, Gojeb and Tis Abay. The studies show that the
stated rivers can generate 523 megawatts of hydro-electric power.
The studies have been given to the Ethiopian Electric Light and
Power Corporation which is undertaking the work on the projects.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said although Ethiopia has water resources that
can generate 30,000 megawatts of hydro-electric power, only 375
megawatt is being exploited. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
