<HEADLINE> Beijing Witnesses Serious Traffic Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 5 (Xinhua) -- A dozen of pedestrians in the
Western District of Beijing were knocked to the ground last night
by a car driven by an intoxicated driver.
</P>
<P>
The traffic accident was caused by Zhang Yongjie, an unemployed
local resident.
</P>
<P>
Zhang's red Xiali model car was proceeding west on Gulou
Street and struck the pedestrians near the Makai Restaurant at
Di'anmen.
</P>
<P>
The car came to halt after colliding with a truck, according to
an eyewitness by the name of Xu.
</P>
<P>
Two victims were hospitalized and the remainder were treated and
released.
</P>
<P>
The case is under investigation and the driver found guilty
will be punished in accordance with law.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has 1.2 million motor vehicles with 1.9 million
drivers. Beijing's Public Security Bureau and traffic
management departments have introduced a series of measures to
enhance the management on motor vehicles, including the
installation of automatic monitoring systems. 
</P>
</TEXT>
