<HEADLINE> Taliban Claim Seizure of Strategic Posts in Northern </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan Taliban militia claimed
Tuesday that they have captured 13 strategic posts in two of the
northern Afghan provinces.
</P>
<P>
Molvi Najibullah, a senior Taliban official based in Peshawar,
capital of Pakistan's North West Frontier Province, told reporters
Tuesday that the Taliban have seized 13 strategic posts from
Persian-speaking Tajik warlord Ahmed Shah Masood in the fighting
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The 13 strategic posts were located in the two northern Afghan
provinces of Takhar and Kundoz, he said.
</P>
<P>
Najibullah also said that the Taliban have succeeded in cutting
communication links between Masood's stronghold of Panjsher Valley
and Takhar province.
</P>
<P>
According to a report by Peshawar-based Sahaar News Agency,
fighting broke out in northern Afghanistan Monday in which heavy
artillery arms were used.
</P>
<P>
However, another news report contradicted the Taliban claim of
capturing Masood's military posts, saying that Masood's forces had
recaptured the areas lost to the Taliban earlier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
