<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Third Plenum of 11th CPC Central Committee (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 5 (Xinhua) -- December 18, 1998 will see the 20th
anniversary of the landmark Third Plenary Session of the 11th
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
The CPC Central Committee issued a circular which was made
public today to list a series of activities to mark the
occasion.
</P>
<P>
The Third Plenum was held in Beijing between December 18 and 22.
</P>
<P>
The major topic of the plenum was to discuss how to shift the
party's focus of work to the development of socialist
modernization. It opened up a new period in China's reforms and
opening to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
The plenum criticized the erroneous policy of two "whatevers,"
or "resolutely upholding whatever policy decisions made by
Chairman Mao and unswervingly following whatever instructions
issued by the late leader."
</P>
<P>
It fully affirmed the necessity of completely and accurately
mastering the scientific system of Mao Zedong Thought, highly
appreciated the discussion on the argument that practice is the
sole criterion for verifying truth and reestablished the
ideological line of emancipating the mind and seeking truth from
facts.
</P>
<P>
The Third Plenum resolutely discarded the slogan of "taking
class struggle as the key link," which no longer suits socialist
society, rejected the erroneous theory of "continued revolution
under the dictatorship of proletariat" and made a strategic
decision on shifting the focus of work of the party and the
people's attention to socialist modernization.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980506.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Third Plenum of 11th CPC Central Committee  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It stated that the state should take a series of new and major
measures to readjust the ratio of already imbalanced national
economy, reform over-concentrated economic management system,
enhance economic cooperation with all other countries on the basis
of mutual benefit and self reliance, introduce up-to-date
technology and equipment from other nations and promote scientific
and educational development. All these laid a foundation for the
Party to formulate the principle of opening to the outside
world and invigorating China's economy.
</P>
<P>
The plenum summed up the experience and lessons drawn by the
CPC, decided to promote democratic centralism and the Party's
regulations and constitution, stressed the importance of
collective leadership of the CPC Central Committee and Party
committees and laid down the tasks of carrying out socialist
democracy and improving a socialist legal system.
</P>
<P>
The immortal merits and achievements of the Third Plenum was to
break away with the long-term trammels of "leftism", enable the
broad masses of cadres and people to shake off the yoke of
personality cult and dogmatism, restore the correct line of
Maxism ideologically, politically and organizationally and end the
situation of lingering on the way forward since the smashing of
the "Gang of four" in 1976.
</P>
<P>
It solved the problem of shifting the focus of the party's
work, the one which failed to be solved since 1957 and brought
order out of chaos.
</P>
<P>
The plenum terminated the situation of fluctuation led by the
erroneous policy of "two whatevers" put forward by the leader who
presided over the work of the CPC Central Committee at that time.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
