<HEADLINE> French Minister Expresses Reservation over New Tax </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 5 (Xinhua) -- French Minister of Industry, Finance and
Economy Dominique Strauss-Kahn Tuesday expressed reservation over
the proposal by the Communist Party to impose a new tax on
speculative capitals.
</P>
<P>
But he agreed that the movement of such capitals are capable of
"destabilizing entire economies" as they did in Southeast Asia
last year.
</P>
<P>
When answering a question from a Communist deputy at the
National Assembly on the possible imposition of tax on speculative
capitals, the minister said that an international cooperation is a
precondition for restricting the flow of speculative capitals,
which are becoming increasingly great in amount.
</P>
<P>
Finance ministers of the Group of Seven (G-7) most
industrialized nations agreed in Washington last month that
greater transparency and greater surveillance were necessary to
control the flow of speculative capitals. 
</P>
