<HEADLINE> Arafat to Brief Mubarak on London Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian National Authority
President Yasser Arafat is to brief his Egyptian counterpart Hosni
Mubarak Thursday on the results of the London talks.
</P>
<P>
Arafat will arrive in Cairo after stopping over in Morocco and
Algeria, Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said intensive mediation by United States
Secretary of State Madeleine Albright between Arafat and Israeli
Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu in London on Monday and Tuesday
has failed to make a breakthrough in Israeli troop pullback from
the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. has tried to persuade Netanyahu to accept its proposal
calling for Israeli withdrawal from 13.1 percent of the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu, citing security reasons, has rejected the proposal,
saying that Israel will withdraw no more than 9 percent of the
West Bank. The Palestinians have reportedly agreed to accept the
U.S. proposal in principle.
</P>
<P>
"The situation remained unchanged: a Palestinian acceptance of
the American initiative and an Israeli rejection of it," Moussa
said.
</P>
<P>
Asked about the impact of the failure of the London talks, he
warned of escalation of tensions in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
"There is no doubt that the failure of the talks will not pass
without having an impact on the angry atmosphere in the area.
Maybe the Israeli side is aware (of it) but does not care," he
added.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian and Israeli negotiators will go on discussing the
issue of Israeli troop pullback from the West Bank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
