<HEADLINE> Vietnam Not to Lower its growth Rate in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, May 5 (Xinhua) -- General Secretary of the Communist
Party of Vietnam (CPV) Le Kha Phieu Tuesday said that Vietnam's
leadership does not think it is necessary to adjust the target of
national economic growth rate in 1998.
</P>
<P>
In a news conference with local and foreign press, Phieu said
in the first months of the year, Vietnam obtained an economic
growth rate of 8.7 percent despite a long drought in the country
and impacts of the financial and monetary crisis in the region.
</P>
<P>
The party chief admitted that Vietnam's economy is facing
challenges, namely the low efficiency of the national economy, low
competitiveness of commodities, and low quantity of processed
farm, forest, husbandry and aquatic products.
</P>
<P>
Phieu, however, pledged further improvement of the investment
environment in order to facilitate foreign investors' business
operations in the country. 
</P>
