<HEADLINE> LIFFE Trades 75 Million Plus Contracts in First </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 5 (Xinhua) - The London International Financial
Futures and Options Exchange (LIFFE) traded 75,975,430 contracts
in the first four months of 1998, up 13 percent on the 1997 figure
of 67,349,585 contracts.
</P>
<P>
During April 1998, LIFFE traded 16,256,840 contracts up 2
percent on April 1997, despite there being 2 less trading days in
April 1998 as against April 1997, the Exchange announced here
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Average daily volume in April 1998 amounted to 812,842 futures
and options contracts, representing an average daily nominal
turnover of 209.13 billion pounds (334.608 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Daniel Hodson, LIFFE's Chief Executive said, "As we approach
Economic and Monetary Union, LIFFE has seen a dramatic increase in
volume in its short term interest rate (STIR) products, an
incredible 58 percent rise year to date on 1997."
</P>
<P>
"This increase further confirms LIFFE's position as the home
exchange for european STIR products and more importantly, the home
exchange for Euro products," he added.
</P>
<P>
With regard to the birth of the Euro last weekend, LIFFE is the
only exchange that trades a three month Euro contract following
the relaunch of its Three Month Euro Futures contract on 30 April
this year.
</P>
<P>
It will also be the first exchange to trade a pan-European
stock index when LIFFE launch a futures contract on the FTSE
Eurotop 100 Index Future on 12th May. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
