<HEADLINE> UN Calls for Proper Management of Food for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations High Commissioner
for Refugees (UNHCR) Tuesday called for the involvement of all
stake-holders in the proper management of food for refugees.
</P>
<P>
UNHCR representative in Zambia Oluseyi Bajulaiye said that the
commissioner experiences a number of problems concerning food
management.
</P>
<P>
Opening a four-day regional workshop on food management and
distribution for refugees, Bajulaiye said that people involved in
food distribution to refugees experience various problems such as
communication breakdown.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the need for dialog and the involvement of local
authorities and women in the distribution of food.
</P>
<P>
Refugees need to become self reliant so that they could
continue feeding themselves even when their rations are cut off,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Bajulaye called for joint efforts to help minimize the
problems of food management and improve the nutrition status of
the refugees.
</P>
<P>
He cited food shortages due to logistic problems like late
deliveries as some of the issues that need immediate attention.
</P>
<P>
The workshop is aimed at upgrading the skills of humanitarian
food distributors among asylum seekers and refugees.
</P>
<P>
UNHCR will soon carry out a nutrition survey in Maheba refugee
camp in Zambia's northwestern province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
