<HEADLINE> Cyprus Reaffirms Commitment to Mideast Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus Foreign Minister Ioannis
Kasoulides Tuesday reaffirmed his government's commitment to the
Mideast peace process and its readiness to contribute actively
to its successful outcome.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a four-day conference of the "Young Leaders
Network," sponsored by the Peres Center for Peace in Israel,
Kasoulides said that Cyprus has recognized the urgent necessity of
taking practical steps to set up a special program of economic and
technical assistance to the Palestinian people.
</P>
<P>
Around 60 youth leaders from Egypt, Jordan, the Palestinian
territories and Israel are attending the conference, which opened
Sunday in Paphos, western coastal town on the island. Former
Israeli Prime Minister Shimon Peres also attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Peres Center for Peace was founded in Israel last year
and its mission is to advance Arab-Israeli cooperation by creating
a wide-range of projects in the fields of economics, education and
social development.
</P>
<P>
Kasoulides described Peres as "one of the great statesmen of
our times with rare political courage and unwavering dedication to
the peace process... who shaped the history of Israel and the
future of the Middle East."
</P>
<P>
"Peres was also one of the first leaders in the Middle East,
who equally recognized that the search for peace and stability in
our region does not end with a comprehensive settlement of the
Middle East problem, and with the solution of the Cyprus problem
as well," he added.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that a united Cyprus would "benefit all the
people of Cyprus and peace and stability in our volatile region,"
adding that it would also affect positively the course of the
peoples and the nations in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has remained divided since 1974 when Turkish troops
invaded and took over the northern third of the island in the wake
of a pro-Athens coup in Nicosia.
</P>
<P>
Kasoulides noted that offering the advanced technical
infrastructure and skilled human resources, Cyprus is in a unique
position to become a meeting point for the peoples and cultures
and a bridge for cooperation among the nations of the region.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
