<HEADLINE> Greece Agrees to Cooperate with U.S. to Stop TV Piracy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Greece Tuesday voiced its willingness
to cooperate with the United States to stop Greek television
stations from broadcasting American programs and movies without
permission.
</P>
<P>
Greek government spokesman Dimitris Reppas said Tuesday that
his country was working with the United States on the issue of
copyright and hoped a solution would be found to the mutual
benefit of both countries.
