<HEADLINE> Peres Supports Creation of Palestinian State </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Former Israeli Prime Minister Shimon
Peres Tuesday expressed his support for the creation of a
Palestinian state, next to the existing Jewish state.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the conference of the "Young Leaders Network,"
which opened Sunday in Paphos, western coastal town in Cyprus,
Peres pointed out that a bi-national state would be an almost
unattainable alternative.
</P>
<P>
"I feel that without a Palestinian state, we (Israel) can't
remain a Jewish state," he said.
</P>
<P>
Peres also stressed the need for the economic development of
the Palestinians, noting that if great economic differences
remain, then the problem will turn from a political to an
economic one.
</P>
<P>
"We need two states but one economy," he said, adding that
what is needed as far as the Israeli-Palestinian problem is
concerned is "political separateness" and "economic integration."
</P>
<P>
Peres also stressed that in a changing world the Middle East
should also change otherwise it would run the danger of being
left behind.
</P>
<P>
He urged young generation not to follow the footsteps of their
predecessors, "not because their fathers were worse than the
children or their parents but because the world has changed."
</P>
<P>
Peres said "there is no longer an objective need for war."
"Every country and every people can reach a new height of
economic development and a new degree of freedom and different
relations can develop among nations," he added.
</P>
<P>
Around 60 young people from Egypt, Jordan, the Palestinian
territories and Israel are attending the conference organized by
the Peres Center for Peace.
</P>
<P>
The center was founded last year in Israel and its mission is
to advance Arab-Israeli cooperation by creating a wide-range of
projects in the fields of economics, education and social
development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
