<HEADLINE> Greek Police Seize Large Quantity of Contraband </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Greek police said Tuesday that they
have seized a large quantity of contraband cigarettes from a
warehouse near the village of Drymos in northern Greece.
</P>
<P>
The contraband cigarettes, estimated at over five million
packets, were discovered on Sunday afternoon when police raided
the warehouse for a stolen car.
</P>
<P>
Police said that they found two trucks with foreign license
plates loaded with contraband cigarettes while the warehouse
itself was stacked high with more cartons.
</P>
<P>
Police believe that it is the biggest ever seizures in Greece
of contraband cigarettes which would have cost Greece 3 billion
drachmas (about 9.68 million U.S. dollars) in lost revenue if sold
on the black market.
</P>
<P>
So far, police have arrested four people including two
Albanians. 
