<HEADLINE> Ciubuc Nominated for New Moldova Premiership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Ion Ciubuc, the caretaker premier
of the Republic of Moldova, was nominated Wednesday for a new term
by the President Petru Lucinschi.
</P>
<P>
Under the constitution and parliamentary regulations, Ciubuc
is empowered to draft the ruling program and the cabinet line-up,
subject to parliament's scrutiny.
</P>
<P>
Parliamentary leader Peter Luchinsky on Monday and Tuesday
consulted with the four parliamentary factions to highlight a
candidate for premiership.
</P>
<P>
The Alliance for Democracy and Reform, the parliamentary
majority formed last month after the March 22 election, consists
of three of the four parliamentary factions -- the Democratic
Convention, the Democratic and Prosperous Moldova Bloc and the
Party of Democratic Forces.
</P>
<P>
The Party of Communists, which ranked the first in the
election, became the only opposition in the parliament.
</P>
<P>
The Democratic Convention nominated Valentin Dolganiuc for the
premiership, while the president said that he would like to see
Ion Ciubuc in the position.
</P>
<P>
The Communist group, which considered that Dolganiuc did "not
have all necessary qualities for taking the premiership", stated
earlier that they would back Ion Ciubuc if he was proposed by the
President.
</P>
<P>
The prerogative to move a candidate for the post belongs to the
head of the state, under the constitution.
</P>
<P>
The new parliament, meeting Wednesday in a plenary session,
will consider the candidacy. 
</P>
