<HEADLINE> Palestinian Gunned Down in West Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, May 6 (Xinhua) -- An unidentified Palestinian was
shot dead in the West Bank on Wednesday, the Jerusalem-based
Palestinian press service JMCC reported.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian, possibly a villager near the city of Nablus,
was gunned down by a Jewish settler near the Eli Settlement on the
highway between Nablus and Ramallah, according to the JMCC.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian police are trying to investigate the incident.
</P>
<P>
Violence erupted during the day in other parts of the West Bank
after the separate talks between U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine
Albright and Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and
Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat in London on Monday and Tuesday
failed to make a breakthrough in Israeli troop pullback from the
West Bank.
</P>
<P>
An Israeli young man aged 28 was stabbed to death by a
Palestinian in the Old City of Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Following the incident, dozens of Palestinian young people
were rounded up near the Damascus Gate of the Old City by the
Israeli security forces for questioning.
</P>
<P>
In Hebron, an Israeli soldier was stabbed by a Palestinian and
rushed to hospital.
</P>
<P>
Israeli troops are stationed in Hebron, most of which is
controlled by the Palestinians, to protect 45 families of Jewish
settlers in the city center. 
</P>
