<HEADLINE> China Set to Become Strongest Economy in Asia: Poll </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 6 (Xinhua) -- China is set to become Asia's
strongest economy, according to the latest Asian Executives Poll
conducted jointly by the Far Eastern Economic Review and CNBC
Asia Business News.
</P>
<P>
Fifty-seven percent of respondents said that China will be the
region's strongest economy in 10 years while 22 percent said that
Japan will remain at the top. Only two percent expected the
Republic of Korea to take first place.
</P>
<P>
The Asian Executives Poll is a weekly fax poll conducted by the
Far Eastern Economic Review and CNBC Asia Business News.
Respondents are chairmen, managing directors and other top
corporate executives in 10 Asian countries. 
