<HEADLINE> India's 1997-98 Exports at 33.97 Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 6 (Xinhua) -- India's 1997-98 total exports were
at 33.97 billion U.S. dollars, increasing by 2.6 percent over the
previous year, said the latest monthly trade data released here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Imports during the period were estimated at 40.77 billion
dollars with the country's trade deficit reaching 6.8 billion
dollars as against 5.55 billion in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Exports during March 1998, the last month of the 1997-98 fiscal
year (April 1, 1997-March 31, 1998), were valued at 3.08 billion
dollars, 6.42 percent lower than the 3.29 billion dollars in the
corresponding period of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Non-oil imports during 1997-98 were estimated at 33.15 billion
dollars, 14.54 percent higher than in 1996-97. 
</P>
