<HEADLINE> India to Test Flight Trainer Aircraft Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 6 (Xinhua) -- India's first all-composite
two-seater trainer aircraft "Hansa-3" is expected to make its
maiden test flight on May 11.
</P>
<P>
Science and Technology Minister Murli Manohar Joshi said at a
press conference here that the trainer aircraft was designed and
built by the country's National Aerospace Laboratories in
Bangalore, capital of Karnataka State in southwestern India.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft, built of light weight composite materials, will
provide a viable, technologically advanced and cost-effective
trainer aircraft for pilots in the country.
</P>
<P>
The new trainer aircraft is estimated to cost 90,000 U.S.
dollars, 20,000 dollars less than the current world price of
similar foreign-made aircraft, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
