CAIRO -- Egyptian Minister of Industry and Mineral Resources
Suleiman Reda Tuesday signed an 8 million U.S. dollars contract
with a Canadian company on exploring and exploiting gold ore for
five years over an area of seven square kilometers in Egypt's
eastern Desert. 
