<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Race Crimes Hit Post-War Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Crimes against foreigners by right-wing
extremists in Germany last year hit a record high in the post-war
era, a German government report said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The number of crimes by far-right groups amounted to 11,719
last year, up 34 percent from 1996, breaking the previous record
of 10,561 cases registered in 1993, German Interior Minister
Manfred Kanther said in the report.
</P>
<P>
The total number of right-wing extremists in Germany was
estimated at about 48,400 by the end of last year, up seven
percent from a year ago. About 7,600 of these people were
classified as militants, up 19 percent when compared with 1996.
</P>
<P>
The report also said that there were about 109 far-right
organizations in Germany last year. The largest parties were the
Republikaner with 15,500 members, followed by the German People's
Union with 15,000 and the National Democratic Party of Germany
with 4,300. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
