<DOCNO> XIE19980506.0116 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets Belgian Parliamentary Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of China's
National People's Congress (NPC) standing committee, met with a
delegation of the Belgian parliament led by Frank Swaelen,
president of the Senate, and Jan Lenssens, vice-president of the
Chamber of Representatives, here today.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China values its ties with Belgium, which is an
important country in the heart of Western Europe, and the site of
the headquarters of the European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
Although the political situations in China and Belgium are
different, the two nations share much in common with regard to the
maintenance of world peace and stability and the development of
their economies, he said.
</P>
<P>
China holds that the world should develop toward
multipolarization, he noted, adding that the EU has a crucial
position and influence in world affairs, and its continuously
strengthened political power and increasingly developed economy
will benefit the process of global multipolarization.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that China and the EU have been cooperating well,
and both sides have devoted great efforts to enhancing the
friendly ties.
</P>
<P>
China welcomes the EU's plan for the single currency, the
"euro", which will be helpful for balancing and stabilizing global
economic activities, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also appreciated the EU's decision to remove China from its
"non-market economy" list.
</P>
<P>
Li provided the visitors with a detailed explanation of China's
system of people's congresses, and its current legislative and
supervisory status. He also introduced them to China's trade
unions, wage system and economic system.
</P>
<P>
He said that China is keen to further foster its friendship
with the parliament of Belgium, and those of the European Council
and of other West European nations, so as to contribute to the
overall development of its relations with those nations.
</P>
<P>
Swaelen thanked the NPC for inviting the delegation to China.
</P>
<P>
The visitors had a far-reaching discussion with Chinese leaders
on matters of common concern, he said, and also saw something of
the Chinese cultural heritage while visiting some scenic spots.
</P>
<P>
The two nations have a tradition of friendship and cooperation,
and Belgium is ready to further strengthen exchanges and
cooperation between the two governments and parliaments, he noted.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Li hosted a welcoming banquet in honor of
the visitors.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is visiting Beijing as guests of the NPC
Standing Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
