<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao SAR Preparatory Committee to Set Up Press Release System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 6 (Xinhua) -- The Preparatory Committee for the
Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR) today decided to
establish a press release system, with a spokesman responsible for
press releases.
</P>
<P>
In addition, systems of collective responsibility and
confidentiality were included in the working rules of the
Preparatory Committee at its first plenum here today.
</P>
<P>
Delivering the first plenum's closing speech, Vice-Premier Qian
Qichen said the establishment of these systems is necessary in
view of the work practice of the Preparatory Committee for the
Hong Kong SAR, and news about the Preparatory Committee will be
delivered through one person, beginning with the first plenum.
</P>
<P>
In order to ensure effective operation of the committee,
members need to abide by all the rules and safeguard the
authority and image of the Preparatory Committee, noted Qian, who
is also chairman of the Preparatory Committee.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that the Preparatory Committee will encourage all
its members to have their say, but they must abide by the
decisions of the committee and maintain its unity when expressing
their views outside, he noted.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the above-mentioned requirement does not mean
that the members cannot give interviews to the mass media; indeed,
they are all able to express their views so long as they uphold
the decisions of the committee.
</P>
<P>
Empowered by the National People's Congress, the Preparatory
Committee for the Macao SAR is responsible for all matters related
to the preparations for the Macao SAR.
</P>
<P>
According to the committee's working rules, the spokesman of
each plenum must be appointed by the chairman or a meeting of the
chairman and vice-chairmen. If necessary, the conveners of the
sub-groups can also give briefings to the press with the
arrangement of the Secretariat. 
</P>
</TEXT>
