<HEADLINE> First Grain Dealer Listed on Shanghai Bourse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 6 (Xinhua) -- The Hunan Jinjian Rice Business
Co. Ltd was listed on the Shanghai Stock Exchange here today to
become the first grain company to issue shares in China.
</P>
<P>
The new shares, with an issuing price of 5.30 yuan per share,
opened at 16.61 yuan and closed at 17.50 yuan, up 221.7
percent. On the first day of its trading, 67 percent of the shares
changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The company's total number of shares is 150 million, including
100 million held by legal persons and 50 million by the public.
</P>
<P>
The new issue is expected to raise 255 million yuan for the
firm's extension project which will give it an annual capacity to
process 100,000 tons of rice.
</P>
<P>
The new issue is of great importance for the current
restructuring of the grain market system in the country, local
experts observe.
</P>
<P>
Hunan is the largest rice producer in China, while Changde
Prefecture, where the company is located, is the one of the
largest rice-producing prefecture in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
