<HEADLINE> Thai Cabinet Okays Central Bank Governor Nomination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, May 6 (Xinhua) -- The Thai cabinet on Wednesday okayed
the nomination of Chatumongol Sonakul as new central bank governor
to replace the resigned Chaiyawat Wibulswasdi.
</P>
<P>
Chatumongol was nominated by Finance Minister Tarrin
Nimmanhaeminda after Chaiyawat resigned under great pressure.
</P>
<P>
Local media hailed Chatumongol's nomination, saying his
integrity, courage, straightforwardness and past record as a
former director general of the Revenue Department suited him to
the challenging task.
</P>
<P>
The new central bank governor said Wednesday that his priority
would be restructuring the central bank and reforming its working
system.
</P>
<P>
He also proposed a group leadership for the central bank.
</P>
<P>
The resignation of Chaiyawat followed a report of an
investigation commission which was assigned to determine the cause
of the disastrous blunders by the central bank during last year's
foreign exchange crisis.
</P>
<P>
The report said Chaiyawat is one of the seven people who should
be responsible for the central bank's failed attempt to use
foreign currency reserves to defend the baht against speculative
attacks.
</P>
<P>
The abortive attempt almost depleted the country's foreign
reserves which plunged from 36.6 billion U.S. dollars to 2.5
billion dollars. 
</P>
