<HEADLINE> Unemployment Slightly Down in Belgium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Belgium saw its jobless rate inch
down by 0.7 percent in the past month, local press reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Belgian television RTBF quoted the Belgian labor ministry as
saying that 430,000 people claimed unemployment benefit by the end
of April, a figure which was dropping slightly.
</P>
<P>
Compared with 12 months ago, however, the decrease was 5.3
percent.
</P>
<P>
Belgium's total unemployment rate now stands at 12.2 percent,
just below the average unemployment rate of the 15-nation European
Union of which Belgium is a member.
</P>
<P>
Unemployment has been a headache for national government
officials and those of the European Commission.
</P>
<P>
The commission, the EU executive body, held a special summit
late last year to address the problem.
</P>
<P>
Commission President Jacques Santer promised that the launch of
Euro would serve as a platform for both employment and
development. 
</P>
