<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen on Work of Macao SAR Preparatory Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier and Chairman of the
Preparatory Committee for the Macao Special Administrative Region
(SAR) Qian Qichen said today that the committee's mission
should be based on achieving the great concept of "one country,
two systems" in Macao.
</P>
<P>
In his speech at the close of the first plenary meeting of the
Preparatory Committee, Qian said that the Basic Law of the Macao SAR
and decisions adopted by the National People's Congress and
its Standing Committee serve as the criteria and foundation for
preparing the establishment of the Macao SAR.
</P>
<P>
Following the establishment of the Preparatory Committee
Tuesday, all the 100 members attended the two-day plenum,
which detailed the committee's work and organized four working
groups in charge of administrative, legal, economic, and social
and cultural affairs, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that the preparations for the Macao SAR are an
important matter which draws the attention of people throughout
the country, particularly the compatriots in Macao.
</P>
<P>
"We must fully practice democracy and solicit opinions from
people from all walks of life in Macao, including all kinds of
different views," Qian said.
</P>
<P>
Stressing openness, the committee should rely on all Macao's
people and mobilize the initiative of people from all walks of
life, he said.
</P>
<P>
He called on the members of the committee to conscientiously
observe the rules of the committee on collective responsibility,
confidentiality and press releases, and safeguard its authority and
image.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the task of the working groups in the near future
is to arrange their working schedules and prepare for the second
plenary meeting of the Preparatory Committee, to be held in early
July.
</P>
<P>
Talking about public security in Macao, Qian pointed out
that the Portugal Macao authorities should be entirely responsible
for handling this problem, and the Preparatory Committee has the
task of putting forth suggestions.
</P>
<P>
Qian expressed the belief that the Preparatory Committee would
score successes, backed by the prosperous motherland, guided by
the "one country, two systems" principle, led by the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, and with the support of
the people of the whole country and the participation by the
compatriots in Macao. 
</P>
</TEXT>
