<HEADLINE> China Promoting Law on Fire Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 6 (Xinhua) -- China's Minister of Public Security,
Jia Chunwang, said here today that a sound implementation of the
law on fire control first requires an extensive promotion campaign
to increase people's awareness of the law and firefighting.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a news conference, Jia said the law on fire control
is a fundamental legal document in China's firefighting campaign,
and departments of public security at each level must take a
leading role in promoting the law by making full use of media
outlets such as newspapers, radio and television.
</P>
<P>
The law on fire control was approved at the second meeting of
the Standing Committee of the Ninth National People's Congress
last month. Chinese President Jiang Zemin issued a decree and
accounced that the law will go into effect on Sept. 1, 1998.
</P>
<P>
Jia said the law not only defines the responsibilities of
related departments for fire control, but also establishes the
obligations of social organizations and citizens in firefighting.
</P>
<P>
The law also emphasizes fire prevention and the key management
work in this aspect by drawing lessons from major fires that have
occurred in the country, while setting out rights, obligations and
responsibilities on all sides in the form of a legal document, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Jia called on firefighting groups at each level to give aid to
the local governments in handling problems related to
firefighting. He issued a reminder that spring is fire season, and
that related departments must prepare for fire prevention.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
