<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ECOMOG Solicits for UN Assistance in S. Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, May 6 (Xinhua) -- The West African peacekeeping force
ECOMOG has solicited the assistance of the United Nations for
logistics and military support in its effort to restore lasting
peace in Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
The chiefs of staff of Nigeria, Ghana and three other
countries that contributed troops to the ECOMOG made the call
Tuesday in Accra, Ghana, in a resolution passed after a two-day
meeting.
</P>
<P>
The chiefs of staff also called for a reinforcement of the
ECOMOG troops by 6,000 more soldiers, according to an earlier
report.
</P>
<P>
ECOMOG troops helped the reinstatement of Sierra Leone's
civilian president Ahmed Tejan Kabbah in March, 10 months after
he was toppled in a military coup which led to the military junta
of Major Paul Johnny Koromah.
</P>
<P>
ECOMOG is still in Sierra Leone to clear out the remaining
forces of Koromah. 
</P>
</TEXT>
