<HEADLINE> China's Top Legislator Meets Seychelles Vice-President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 6 (Xinhua) -- China is satisfied with its
long-term and stable relations with the Seychelles, said Li Peng,
chairman of the National People's Congress (NPC) Standing
Committee, here today.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with Seychelles Vice-President James Michel,
Li recalled his visit to Seychelles a year ago, saying that the
trip had left a "beautiful impression" on him.
</P>
<P>
Since the two countries forged diplomatic ties, he said,
bilateral relations have been good and personal contacts have been
on rise, while economic and trade cooperation have been fruitful.
</P>
<P>
The two nations have also undertaken close cooperation on
international issues, Li said.
</P>
<P>
He said he felt happy that the Seychelles has maintained
lasting stability and its economy has continued to develop. Li
said he wished the country even more achievements in their
national construction.
</P>
<P>
Michel said Li's last visit to the Seychelles and other African
countries had played an important role in promoting Africa-China
relations.
</P>
<P>
China is a good friend of the Seychelles and all of Africa, he
noted.
</P>
<P>
China had made positive contributions to the liberation of
Africa, Michel said, adding that it will continue to contribute
greatly to the development of Africa in the forthcoming century.
</P>
<P>
Ding Shisun, vice-chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, was
present at the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
