<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Multinational Firm Sets Up Regional Headquarters in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Unilever Corp., a British-Dutch
joint venture, today set up its regional headquarters in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Unilever is the third multinational firm this year to set up
regional headquarters in this leading industrial and commercial
center of China, following Microsoft and Kodak from the United
States.
</P>
<P>
"The establishment of new headquarters indicates our confidence
in the long-term development of China," said an official from the
firm.
</P>
<P>
Unilever, one of the largest daily necessities producers in the
world, has invested more than 640 million U.S. dollars in China.
</P>
<P>
In the past several years, 55 of the world's top 100
multinational firms have launched 129 projects in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The change from solely manufacturing products in China to
setting up regional headquarters also shows the improvement of
China's investment environment, according to local government
sources.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey by the Shanghai government shows that over 90
percent of foreign-funded firms are optimistic about their future
development in China and 83 percent of them plan to increase
investment over the next five years.
</P>
<P>
To improve its competitiveness in the Chinese market, Unilever
also plans to work in cooperation with the Shanghai Institute of
Organic Chemistry to produce cosmetics and detergent using
traditional Chinese medicine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
