<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji Meets with Chile's Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 6 (Xinhua)-- China will maintain its friendly and
cooperative relationship with Chile as it has always done, Premier
Zhu Rongji said here this afternoon while meeting with Chilean
Foreign Minister Jose Miguel Insulza.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that China values its cooperative relationship with
Chile and considers it an important partner in Latin America.
</P>
<P>
There exists great potential and a promising future for the two
countries to bolster their cooperation on the basis of good
political relations, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
China hopes to make joint efforts with Chile to establish a
relationship of long-term stability and mutual benefit, which is
oriented towards the 21st century, Zhu added.
</P>
<P>
Insulza expressed his appreciations for the social and economic
development and the reforms of China in recent years, saying that
China is now an important trade partner in Asia.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean government hopes to make further efforts to enhance
bilateral trade and its economic relationship to a new level, the
visiting foreign minister added.  
</P>
