<HEADLINE> State Council Meeting Hears Reports on Ecology, AIDS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 6 (Xinhua) -- The Executive Meeting of the State
Council, presided over by Premier Zhu Rongji, heard two reports
today on improving the country's environment and AIDS prevention
and treatment.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, Vice-Minister of the State Development Planning
Commission Wang Chunzheng explained an outline on improving the
environment, and Minister of Health Zhang Wenkang delivered a
report on the prevention and treatment of AIDS.
</P>
<P>
Since China's reform and opening-up, the national economy has
continued its rapid growth. However, some localities have ignored
the protection of natural resources. As a result, the environment
is deteriorating and sustained social and economic growth has been
seriously undermined, participants at the meeting said.
</P>
<P>
In this sense, it is a critical and pressing task for China to
improve the environment by curbing soil erosion through planting
trees and grass, halting desertification and developing ecological
agriculture.
</P>
<P>
With an eye on long-term ecological benefits, the priority
should be placed on short-term goals, according to the
participants. In addition, the relationship between national
interests and local interests should be handled better.
</P>
<P>
Hearing the report on AIDS prevention and treatment, the
participants said that the spread of AIDS has drawn the attention
of governments of various countries, and the disease has become a
major health and social problem.
</P>
<P>
In China, AIDS is spreading quickly. Governments at all levels
should intensify efforts to improve the relevant regulations, map
out work plans, increase input and further raise the awareness of
the public about the disease, according to participants.  
</P>
</TEXT>
