<HEADLINE> Two S. Africans Jailed for Over 340 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Two Johannesburg men were sent
to prison for a combined total of more than 340 years on Tuesday
for conducting a reign of terror in the metropolis' northwestern
suburbs.
</P>
<P>
Charges against Frank Motsusi, 21, and Ernest Mosadi, 29,
included murder, attempted murder, robbery, kidnaping, hijacking
and unlawful possession of firearms.
</P>
<P>
Between June and December 1995, the two robbed various
restaurants, pizza shops and video outlets in five suburbs of
Johannesburg. Among the cases were the murder of a bottle store
owner and the murder of a man whose gun they had taken.
</P>
<P>
"They were having an absolute royal time,... Every Friday or
Saturday night they would go out and rob one or other place. They
were very violent and that's the reason why the judge was so
upset and gave them such high sentences," said a police captain,
who was celebrating Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
The arrests of the two in December 1995, while they were
trying to rob a shop, brought an end to a crime spree that made
ordinary residents in the neighborhood too afraid to leave their
homes at weekends.
</P>
<P>
Motsusi was sentenced to 215 years on more than 20 charges,
and Mosadi was sentenced to 126 years on 16 charges. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
