<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Meets Members of Macao Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Meeting members of the Preparatory
Committee for the Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR),
President Jiang Zemin said here today that the committee's
founding indicates that preparations for Macao's return to the
motherland have entered a new stage.
</P>
<P>
The 100-member Preparatory Committee was set up Tuesday, and
the members had their first plenary meeting during the past two
days.
</P>
<P>
"Macao's return is another great matter for the Chinese nation
following Hong Kong's return to the motherland," said Jiang, also
general secretary of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
China is experiencing a crucial period of development at the
turn of a new century, Jiang noted. The 15th CPC National Congress
held last fall and the First Session of the Ninth National
People's Congress held in March of this year have outlined the
country's promising prospects.
</P>
<P>
"In the new century, we will not only build our country into a
modern and strong country, but will achieve the great cause of
reunifying the motherland in the end," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the great concept of "one country, two systems"
created by Deng Xiaoping is the fundamental principle to resolve
the questions concerning Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
"The practices in Hong Kong over the past 10 months since its
return to the motherland have shown that the principle is entirely
correct," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that Macao's return will also follow the
principle of "one country, two systems" and "a high degree of
autonomy". And Macao residents will be able to manage the internal
affairs of the Macao SAR in accordance with the Basic Law of Macao
SAR.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that Macao people can administer Macao well, and
our compatriots in Macao can surely maintain Macao's social
stability and economic growth and create a more splendid future
for Macao," he said.
</P>
<P>
Macao's return will produce another good example for the
concept of "one country, two systems," and will be conducive to
resolving the Taiwan question and enventually achieving the entire
reunification of the motherland, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The Preparatory Committee is facing an arduous workload because
Macao's return is less than 600 days away, he said, adding that he
expects the committee members to display their wisdom and the mass
of Macao residents to take an active part in contributing to the
founding of the Macao SAR on December 20, 1999.
</P>
<P>
Senior leaders Li Peng, Zhu Rongji, Li Ruihuan, Hu Jintao, Wei
Jianxing and Li Lanqing were among those present at today's
ceremony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
