<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Broadly lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange dipped further Wednesday on continued
selling pressure as investors found no incentive to support the
market coupled with the weaker local unit -- the ringgit against
the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
The local unit closed lower Wednesday at 3.7740/890 against the
greenback compared to 3.6900/000 on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The market breached the 600 points level after the first few
minutes of trading.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index fell 23.78
points or 3.91 percent to 584.62, the all-share Emas Index eased
5.35 points to 147.51, the Industrial Index was 27.85 points lower
at 1,081.92 and the Second Board Index also shed 3.21 points to
128.17.
</P>
<P>
Losers outpaced gainers by 605 to 86 while 115 counters were
unchanged and 110 others untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover increased to 145.473 million shares worth
384.724 million ringgit (about 101.94 million U.S. dollars) from
127.186 million shares valued at 314.223 million ringgit (about
83.259 million U.S. dollars) on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover rose to 133.024 million shares worth
365.899 million ringgit (about 96.952 million U.S. dollars) from
118.440 million shares valued at 301.035 million ringgit (about
79.765 million U.S. dollars) on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover was higher at 12.449 million shares
worth 18.825 million ringgit (about 4.988 million U.S. dollars)
from Tuesday's 8.746 million shares valued at 13.188 million
ringgit (about 3.494 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market volume added to 5.120 million shares worth 15.069
million ringgit (about 3.992 million U.S. dollars) from Tuesday's
4.200 million shares valued at 13.897 million ringgit (about 3.682
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 7.861
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products
11.718 million shares, construction 12.431 million shares,
trading/service 38.432 million shares, infrastructure 1.518
million shares, finance 22.060 million shares, hotels 500,000
shares, properties 17.113 million shares, plantation 4.894 million
shares, mining 802,600 shares, trusts 167,000 shares, closed/fund
77,000 shares and loans 15.449 million shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
