<HEADLINE> Daimler, Chrysler in Talks for Possible Merger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Daimler-Benz AG confirmed
Wednesday that it has entered into talks with U.S. carmaker
Chrysler on a possible mega-merger.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued Wednesday morning, Daimler-Benz said the
merger could take the form of a share swap, with the two forming a
joint company.
</P>
<P>
However, Daimler also stressed that there was no certainty that
an agreement could be reached.
</P>
<P>
The two companies had also agreed not to disclose further
details until the merger talks were completed, Daimler said.
</P>
<P>
With the statement, Daimler was responding to a report in
Wednesday's edition of the Wall Street Journal which said that
Chrysler's directors were to discuss the estimated
35-billion-dollar merger proposal later Wednesday at a regular
board meeting. Daimler's board was also due to discuss it this
week.
</P>
<P>
The report pointed out that the two companies had made
significant progress in their talks and a decision could be
reached soon.
</P>
<P>
If a deal was done, it would be a mega-merger combining
Germany's largest industrial concern with the third largest
U.S. carmaker, which is unprecedented in strategy and size.
</P>
</TEXT>
