<HEADLINE> 1 Israeli Soldier Stabbed in Hebron </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, May 6 (Xinhua) -- An Israeli soldier was stabbed
Wednesday morning in the West Bank city of Hebron, Israeli army
said.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli border guard soldier was stabbed at the zone
between H1 and H2 in Hebron and rushed to hospital, the army said
in a press release.
</P>
<P>
Hebron is the only city in the West Bank that houses about 45
families of Jewish settlers and some Israeli military troops are
stationed there to protect them.
</P>
<P>
H1 areas are zones where the Palestinians are living and H2
areas are the territory occupied by the Jewish settlers in Hebron.
</P>
<P>
According to another report, an Israeli student was stabbed to
death in Arab East Jerusalem on his way to pray at the Western
Wall on the same day.
</P>
<P>
The incidents came after the failure of London talks, during
which Israel and the Palestinians remained locked in the dispute
over the size of further Israeli troop pullback from the West
Bank. 
