But drought is still worsening in some areas, such as the
northeastern Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, northwestern Jilin
Province, southwestern Sichuan Province and Yunnan Province,
officials in the headquarters said.
</P>
<P>
The headquarters reported that the rainfall is not only
beneficial to crops in the field, primarily wheat, but also for
planting autumn crops, according to today's Economic Daily.
</P>
<P>
However, the rainfall is only marginally helpful for planting
rice, the paper reported.
</P>
<P>
Statistics on May 4 show that the drought-affected area has
reached 2.1 million hectares. The drought has also caused drinking
water shortages for 11.5 million people and 9.8 million livestock.
</P>
<P>
The headquarters urged local governments to prepare for a
worsening situation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
