<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chongqing To Develop Housing Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing, metropolis in southwest
China, plans to start building 10 million sq m of residential
houses this year, as a move to develop the real estate industry
into one of the city's economic growth areas.
</P>
<P>
The city will complete construction of 5.8 million sq m of
housing this year, nearly twice the average during the Eighth
Five-Year Plan period (1991-1995).
</P>
<P>
The per capita housing space of Chongqing residents will
increase to nine sq m after the completion of the new scheme.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Chongqing residents will find it much easier to
apply for bank mortgage loans to purchase houses, since local
commercial banks have set aside 400 million to 600 million yuan of
housing loan, in addition to the 50 million yuan in loans provided
by the city's housing fund administration center.
</P>
<P>
Starting from July 1, 1998, local residents will be able to
sell their houses freely on the market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
