<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Large-scale Power Grids To Be Connected by 2020 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Almost all of China's power grids
will be connected before 2020 to make power exchanges possible
nationwide, a senior official said here today.
</P>
<P>
The fast-growing economy has brought a new stage in power
development characterized by large capacity and large grids, said
Huo Ji'an, deputy general manager of the State Power Grid
Development Co. Ltd., and that China has six large grids and a
group of provincial ones with 567,000 kilometers (km) of
transmission lines.
</P>
<P>
He said the Three Gorges Power Station will allow for the
connection of power grids nationwide. The station will provide
power for areas in central and north China, and Sichuan grids, and
help form the Great Central China Power Grid spanning a distance
of 2,000 km from east to west. The grid will still serve as a link
to the grids in north, northwest and south China.
</P>
<P>
By 2000, the framework of various inter-provincial grids will
take shape, involving perfection of the 500 kilovolt (kv) and 330
kv grids.
</P>
<P>
Huo said that the Three Gorges Power Station will be completed
by 2009, and a 500 kv project ranging from there to the power
grids in central and north China, and Sichuan Province will be
established with 9,100 km of DC and AC transmission lines.
</P>
<P>
Thermal power-production bases in Shanxi, Shaanxi and Jiangxi
provinces will ensure large power supplies for Beijing, Tianjin,
Tangshan, Baoding and other cities in northeast China, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
