<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade Increases in Eastern Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Although it too was affected by the
Southeast Asian financial crisis, east China's Shandong Province
has nonetheless had some slight growth in foreign trade in the
first quarter of the year.
</P>
<P>
Foreign trade was worth 4.38 billion US dollars during the
period, up 2.9 percent on a year-on-year basis.
</P>
<P>
Imports amounted to 1.88 billion US dollars, up 0.6 percent,
and exports, 2.5 billion US dollars, up 4.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Because six of the province's major trade partners, including
the Republic of Korea and Japan, were affected by the financial
crisis, exports to these countries were down 9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Machinery, garments, textiles, and shoes still account for most
of the goods traded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
