<HEADLINE> Large Township Enterprise Groups Blooming in South China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 6 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong Province
is giving an impetus to the growth of large and medium-sized
township enterprises, which have developed rapidly in recent years
in the province.
</P>
<P>
The province has now established 350 township enterprise groups
by merging major township enterprises. Thirtytwo of them have been
approved by the Ministry of Agriculture as "China's major township
enterprise groups."
</P>
<P>
Guangdong now has 369 township enterprises each with annual
business revenues of more than 100 million yuan. The Kelon
Electrical Appliance Co. Ltd. in Shunde City, for instance, has
annual business revenues of 5.57 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Shantou City set a goal of developing large township
enterprises, brand-name products and pillar industries. As a
result, 58 township enterprises were approved by the Ministry of
Agriculture as large or medium-sized enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that the appearance of large township enterprise
groups signifies an overall development of the township
enterprises in Guangdong and that the next phase will focus on
the improvement of product quality. 
</P>
</TEXT>
