<HEADLINE> 1 Israeli Stabbed to Death In East Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, May 6 (Xinhua) -- An Israeli was stabbed to death
early Wednesday morning in Arab East Jerusalem, Israeli police
said.
</P>
<P>
The incident came as the Israeli and Palestinians remained
locked in the dispute over the scope of further Israeli troop
redeployment in the West Bank after the failure of the London
meetings Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Israeli military reinforcements were brought up to the area
following the incident while dozens of Palestinian young people
were rounded up near the Damascus Gate of the Old City by Israeli
security forces.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli police have not identified the victim, but said
efforts would be made to find out the killer.
</P>
<P>
This was the second killing occurred in East Jerusalem so far
this year. A 30-year-old Jewish student was stabbed to death in
February when he was on his way to a synagogue in the Ramat Shilmo
neighborhood in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Last November, a Jewish student was shot to death in the Muslim
quarter of the Old City. Since then, Israel has beefed up police
presence and set up more police stations there.
</P>
<P>
East Jerusalem has been at the center of Israeli-Palestinian
disputes as Israel claims its sovereign control over the whole
city, while the palestinians want it as the capital of their
future Palestinian State. 
</P>
</TEXT>
