<HEADLINE> Jiangsu Sees Growth in Foreign Trade, Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, May 6 (Xinhua) -- The latest statistics show that the
total foreign trade volume of east China's Jiangsu Province
increased by 15.5 percent in the first two months of this year, to
stand at 2.78 billion US dollars-worth.
</P>
<P>
Direct overseas investment in Jiangsu also expanded by 11.6
percent on a year-on-year basis, to reach 680 million US dollars,
according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
Located on the Yangtze River Delta, Jiangsu has witnessed rapid
economic growth over the past few years, due to sustained efforts
in reform and opening-up.
</P>
<P>
The province's exports reached 1.99 billion US dollars-worth in
the first two months, a surge of 25.3 percent from the same period
of last year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, overseas investment has been increasing steadily in
local development zones and major economic cities over the past
few years.
</P>
<P>
In the first quarter of this year, this capital of the province
approved 46 more foreign-funded enterprises, which involve a total
of 140 million US dollars in investment.
</P>
<P>
The combined exports of foreign-funded enterprises account for
44 percent of the city's total.
</P>
<P>
The Suzhou Industrial Park in Suzhou City, which was jointly
established by the Chinese and Singaporean governments in 1995,
has also witnessed an increase in direct overseas investment in
recent years, reaching 1.35 billion US dollars. However, its
aggregate contracted investment from abroad was 4.15 billion US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Some 18 of the world's Top 500 multinational companies have set
up joint ventures or wholly-owned enterprises in the Suzhou
Industrial Park.  
</P>
</TEXT>
