<HEADLINE> Publications Mark Anniversary of Beijing University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Beijing University has published
more than 30 varieties of books and electronic publications to
mark its May 4 centennial.
</P>
<P>
The books feature the 100-year development of the
university. They include a photo album, a collection of Chinese
essays, a commemorative VCD, and a selection of experts'
handwriting.
</P>
<P>
The photo album, "Beijing University," includes 400 historical
photographs which show the school's history and Chinese leaders'
concern over its development.
</P>
<P>
"Famous People and Beijing University" offers true stories
about the university and Mao Zedong, Zhou Enlai, Deng Xiaoping and
well-known cultural experts and artists.
</P>
<P>
The five million-word "Centennial Essay Collection" includes
abundant papers and documents about the school's research
development in the fields of literature, history, philosophy,
language and archeology during the last 100 years.
</P>
<P>
Beijing University was established in 1898, the first national
university set up by the central government. 
</P>
