<HEADLINE> Philippine Exports Grow by 24 Percent in 1st Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Philippines' exports of goods for the
first quarter of 1998 increased by 23.8 percent to 6.82 billion
U.S. dollars from the year-ago level, the National Statistics
Office said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
It said receipts for March alone were 2.47 billion dollars,
23.6 percent higher than the same period last year. The earnings
went up by 11 percent on a month-on-month base.
</P>
<P>
The National Statistics Office said that in the first three
months this year, electronics and components was the largest
export item with a 48.3 percent share in the total volume. It was
followed by articles of apparel and clothing accessories, input,
output and peripheral units and ignition wiring sets.
</P>
<P>
The United States remained the largest market for Philippine
goods, accounting for 32.9 percent of the total exports volume.
</P>
