<HEADLINE> China's Foreign Trade Minister Meets Spain's Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 6 (Xinhua) -- China's Minister of Foreign Trade
and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC) Shi Guangsheng said that China
is willing to join hands with Spain to achieve a trade balance
between the two countries and is eyeing the comprehensive
development of bilateral trade ties.
</P>
<P>
Shi made the remarks in today's meeting with Spain's Foreign
Minister, Abel Matutes.
</P>
<P>
Shi said that China and Spain have smoothly developed
cooperation in various fields since the two nations forged
diplomatic ties 25 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Spain is an important trading partner of China, Shi added.
</P>
<P>
Spain's participation in China's economic construction is
welcome, Shi said, and he hopes the European country will win a
broad market in China.
</P>
<P>
China wants to jointly develop international markets such as
Latin America along with Spain, Shi stressed, adding that this
would be conducive to economic development in Latin America and
also serve Sino-Spanish economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Matutes said that Spain and China enjoy sound political ties
and broad potential for economic and trade relations.
</P>
<P>
The Spanish government encourages its enterpreneurs to invest
in China, Matutes said, and that he hopes China provides sound
conditions for these investors.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister said he expected the opening of the next
meeting of the mixed economic and trade committee between the two
countries, scheduled for late this year, to discuss cooperation in
the fields of infrastructure, environmental protection and
agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Matutes stressed his government's support for China's early
entry to the World Trade Organization, for which Shi expressed his
appreciation.  
</P>
