<HEADLINE> WTO Urged to Accept China as Official Member </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The International Council of
Former Heads of Government (ICFHG) Tuesday urged the World Trade
Organization (WTO) to accelerate the process of negotiation for
admitting China to official membership.
</P>
<P>
The council made the appeal in a communique released Tuesday by
the 16th annual meeting of the group which ended here Tuesday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The communique highly praised China for her efforts to contain
the Asian financial crisis and stablize the Asian financial market.
</P>
<P>
The ICFHG expressed its appreciation of China's decision not to
devalue its currency which played an essential role in containing
the crisis.
</P>
<P>
The international body also urged the "Group of Seven" to
accept China as a member country.
</P>
<P>
The communique suggested the Group of Seven take effective
measures to limit the manufacture and exports of weapons.
</P>
<P>
Song Jian, vice chairman of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference, was invited as a special guest by the
16th annual meeting of ICFHG which started last Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Song made a speech introducing China's economic development and
the situation of the Asian financial crisis. 
