<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 400 Evacuated as Volcano Erupts Costa Rica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, May 5 (Xinhua) -- At least 400 people were evacuated
when a volcano on Costa Rica's Mount El Arenal erupted and sent
columns of ash and smoke into the skies on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Seismological Observatory reported three major eruptions
from the 5,389-foot (1,633 meters) volcanic peak Tuesday
afternoon. But there were no immediate reports of injury.
</P>
<P>
The local government declared an emergency in the region
surrounding El Arenal, the country's highest mountain. The region
is a tourist resort with some thermal baths and several
hotels. Authorities closed all access roads to the volcano on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The volcano, located 100 kilometers north of San Jose, first
erupted on June 29, 1968, killing 95 people. The last big eruption
in 1993 caused no deaths. 
</P>
</TEXT>
