<HEADLINE> Colombia Reports Deficit Rise for First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTA FE DE BOGOTA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The Colombian government
Tuesday reported a rise in its financial deficit for the first
quarter of the year due in part to advance payment for accrued
interest of foreign debts.
</P>
<P>
According to the Superior Council of Financial Policies, the
deficit soared to two trillion pesos (1.5 billion U.S. dollars),
or 1.5 percent of the gross domestic product (GDP), compared with
1.29 percent for the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
