<HEADLINE> "Daughter of Dunhuang" Becomes Head of Dunhuang Academy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Fan Jinshi, a 60-year-old specialist
on China's Dunhuang Caves, has become the first woman to head the
Dunhuang Academy, replacing Duan Wenjie who has been named
Honorary President.
</P>
<P>
Fan, who is a native of Shanghai, is a graduate of Beijing
University and has earned the title the "Daughter of Dunhuang" because
of decades of work in the desert city of Dunhuang in Gansu
Province, northwest China.
</P>
<P>
The Dunhuang Academy was set up in 1944 as a research insitute
and Chang Shuhong, a painter who was studying in France, was made
its first president.
</P>
<P>
The academy now has more than 140 staff members working in a
dozen institutes. Fan's husband also works in the academy.
</P>
<P>
The couple have two sons.  
</P>
