<HEADLINE> Ferrari Boosted by New Exhaust System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Formula one team Ferrari said on
Tuesday they will introduce a radical exhaust system in Sunday's
Spanish Grand Prix.
</P>
<P>
This might boost the team's number one racer, Michael
Schumacher's hopes of catching championship leaders McLaren.
</P>
<P>
The exhaust system sees the pipe exit at the top of the rear
bodywork rather than under the rear diffuser. This makes the car
faster as it is more stable under braking and acceleration.
</P>
<P>
Ferrari will also introduce new rear suspension geometry, a
more efficient fuel-injection system and a new rear wing in a bid
to close the gap on McLaren.
</P>
<P>
McLaren have a clear lead over Ferrari in the constructors'
championship and Mika Hakkinen leads from McLaren teammate David
Coulthard in the drivers' standings. Schumacher is third. 
</P>
