<HEADLINE> Prison in Managua Closed due to Meningitis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The Nicaraguan Health Ministry
closed a prison in Managua Tuesday for one week due to an outbreak
of meningitis.
</P>
<P>
The disease killed two prisoners and sent three others to the
hospital.
</P>
<P>
Visits by prisoners' relatives have been suspended and every
one has been prohibited from entering or leaving a police station
where the contagious virus was reportedly discovered, the ministry
said.
</P>
<P>
Epidemiologist Fabiola Prado said the outbreak is under
control, but the quarantine is still in effect to prevent the
meningitis bacteria from spreading.
</P>
<P>
The Health Ministry has provided medical treatment and
immunizations to 199 prisoners and 20 policemen in order to
prevent the spread of the virus.
</P>
<P>
Of the seven cases of meningitis discovered in the capital city
this week, four people have died. Last year the disease killed
five persons in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
