<HEADLINE> Chilean Forestry Exports Drop Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Chilean forestry exports reached
253.2 million U.S. dollars in the first two months of the year, a
17.1 percent reduction over the same period in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Jose Antonio Prado, executive director of the National Forestry
Corporation, said the reduction was attributed to the lack of
demand from Asian countries since the recent financial crises
occurring in Asia have interrupted normal business activities.
</P>
<P>
Wood products are the main exports of Chile and Asian countries
are the main buyers.
</P>
<P>
Exports to South Korea reached only 12 million dollars in
January and February, which represents a 75 percent reduction,
while Japan's imports went down 25.4 percent to reach 49.20
million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
