<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Survey Reveals Diverse Consumption Trends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 6 (Xinhua) -- A recent survey indicates
diverse consumption trends for residents in Beijing, Shanghai and
Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
Beijingers tend to purchase more daily necessities, with
Shanghainese preferring to buy financial portfolios and Guangzhou
residents opting for housing, according to the survey.
</P>
<P>
The survey, conducted by the Shanghai Statistical Bureau, shows
that Beijingers purchased five percent more daily necessities last
year than in 1996, with figures for Shanghai and Guangzhou
dropping by two percent and seven percent.
</P>
<P>
Shanghainese established average financial portfolios of 151
yuan, some 47 percent higher than in Guangzhou and move than 80
percent than in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou spent some 520 yuan on housing purchases, some 12
times the figure for Shanghai and 1.3 times levels in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The three cities enjoyed the highest per capita income levels
in the country. The 1997 per capita income for Guangzhou residents
stood at 10,200 yuan, with the figures for Shanghai and Beijing
hitting 8,439 yuan and 7,813 yuan respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
