<HEADLINE> Highlights of Beijing-based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- China will celebrate the 20th anniversary of the Third
Plenary Session of the 11th Central Committee of the Communist
Party of China(CPC) on December 18 this year.
</P>
<P>
The plenary session was of vital importance in the history of
both the Party and the state, as it reestablished the ideological
line of emancipating the mind and seeking truth from facts,
according to a circular of the CPC Central Committee which was
made public yesterday.
</P>
<P>
-- An editorial in the paper hails the setting up of the
Preparatory Committee for the Macao Special Administrative
Region(SAR) yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Now that the Preparatory Committee has been founded, the work
to establish the Macao SAR has been ushered into a new state, the
editorial states.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- Announcing the start of preparatory work for the Macao SAR,
Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen said the Preparatory Committee
will face a great deal of urgent work and that he hopes the
committee members will make a combined effort for the smooth
transition and transfer of power in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Qian, also chairman of the Preparatory Committee, said that
realizing the return of Macao in accordance with the "one country,
two systems" principle is another significant event for the
Chinese nation after Hong Kong's return.
</P>
<P>
-- Premier Zhu Rongji has stressed the inevitability and
urgency to restructure the nation's grain marketing system at a
national work conference on restructuring the grain marketing
system held between April 27-29.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said, reform must be carried out in line with the
principles of separation of administrative functions from
State-owned grain companies, storage from management, central from
local responsibilities and new from old accounts, as well as
improving the pricing system for the grain market.
</P>
<P>
"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The direct secure telephone communication link between
Chinese President Jiang Zemin and Russian President Boris Yeltsin
has been officially commissioned.
</P>
<P>
-- China has documented 9,970 cases of human immunodeficiency
virus(HIV) by the end of March, with 290 cases involving fully
developed acquired immune deficiency syndrome (AIDS) and 173
patients having died from the disease. 
</P>
