<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nanning City Improving Air Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Air quality in Nanning, capital of
south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, now has greatly
been improved.
</P>
<P>
The city government has allocated substantial funding in recent
years for afforestation to control air pollution.
</P>
<P>
The landscaped coverage in the city was 36.4 percent in 1997,
with per capita greenery standing at 6.7 square meters. Nanning
is, in fact, recognized as one of the nation's park cities.
</P>
<P>
The city's environment department has severely punished
chemical plants and sugar factories causing heavy pollution, and
has installed industrial waster and air treatment equipment. Some
75 small enterprises creating heavy pollution have been closed
over the past three years.
</P>
<P>
The city sits in a basin surrounded by mountains which restrict
wind velocity needed to remove polluted air.
</P>
<P>
Nanning has over 300,000 motor vehicles and 140,000
motorcycles. Motor vehicle emissions are the major culprit in air
pollution.  
</P>
</TEXT>
