<HEADLINE> U.S., Russian Securities Industry Enhances Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The Securities Industry Association
of the United States signed an agreement with the self-regulatory
organization of Russia's securities industry here Tuesday to
enhance their cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The SIA has nearly 800 securities firms under its umbrella,
including investment banks, broker-dealers and mutual fund
companies, while the National Association of the Securities Market
Participants of Russia numbers over 800 member firms.
</P>
<P>
The SIA and the NAUFOR intend to cooperate in developing
training and continuing education programs for the management and
employees of member firms of both organizations.
</P>
<P>
They will also increase the exchange of information, organize
joint seminars or conferences and forums in which both
organizations can meet to discuss common issues, according to
the SIA. 
